\
Blog Content Considerations and Suggestions:\
\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720
\ls2\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}Identify a Need 
\b0 - Try to name a need or problem a reader might have. Identify concrete needs that you\'92re aiming for the post to fullfill and questions that you want the post to answer. (e.g. 
\i How to
\i0  prune roses in 3 steps, get rid of aphids, attract warblers, etc)\
\pard\tx720\pardeftab720
\cf0 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720
\ls3\ilvl0
\b \cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}Picture a Reader
\b0  \'96 Imagine a particular person who may be reading your post. Keep their situation, needs, questions and challenges in front of you as you write and even pictures them when you choose a topic. In this way you don\'92t just end up with abstract topics \'96 but are closer to writing concrete and applicable posts that will connect with readers. (e.g. A local Chestnut Hill Gardener, a professional arborist, middle school teacher, etc)\
\pard\tx720\pardeftab720
\cf0 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720
\ls4\ilvl0
\b \cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}Write Something that Matters to You 
\b0 - When something matters to you it shines through in the way you communicate about it and this has a way of engaging others who also think it matters. \
\pard\tx720\pardeftab720

\b \cf0 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720
\ls5\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}Write Something Topical 
\b0 - Write on a topic that is currently popular, relevant to your community, or seasonality (e.g. Holiday, spring planting, etc). Or consider writing a recap of a recent class or event - this entices people to sign up for future events. \
\pard\tx720\pardeftab720

\b \cf0 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720
\ls6\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}Keep it Concise
\b0  \'96 Posts that really hone in on one particular topic and communicate one main idea tend to do best. There is nothing wrong with writing long sweeping posts that cover many things, but do keep in mind that most people\'92s reading style online is to scan content, flip between pages and not to dwell on any one thing for too long. If your topic needs to be covered in length, consider writing a mini series of posts.\
\pard\tx720\pardeftab720
\cf0 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720
\ls7\ilvl0
\b \cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}Call to Action 
